      <Content>&lt;p&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;Ok, first let me be really clear, I’m not a &lt;a href="http://www.jetbrains.com/index.html" target="_blank"&gt;JetBrains&lt;/a&gt; fan boy.     &lt;br /&gt;Yes, I use &lt;a href="http://www.jetbrains.com/resharper/index.html" target="_blank"&gt;ReSharper&lt;/a&gt; and yes, I also use &lt;a href="http://www.jetbrains.com/teamcity/index.html" target="_blank"&gt;TeamCity&lt;/a&gt; at home as my &lt;a href="http://martinfowler.com/articles/continuousIntegration.html" target="_blank"&gt;Continuous Integration&lt;/a&gt; server for some of my projects.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;I also use &lt;a href="http://confluence.public.thoughtworks.org/display/CCNET/Welcome+to+CruiseControl.NET" target="_blank"&gt;Cruise Control.Net&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href="https://hudson.dev.java.net/" target="_blank"&gt;Hudson&lt;/a&gt; in other projects (sometimes both in the same project, to do different things)&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;But the guys from JetBrains do really good products, ex: TeamCity is ,IMHO, the most friendly CI server of the three to set up and ReSharper makes practicing TDD or BDD not just possible but highly enjoyable.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;So when I came across RubyMine a few months ago I decided to give it a try. I have been using &lt;a href="http://blog.dynamicprogrammer.com/2008/01/03/TheRubyAndRailsIDEThatIMiss.aspx" target="_blank"&gt;different IDE’s and Editors&lt;/a&gt; on my adventures into the Ruby world but even when I found some of them really good I never really feel at home.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.netbeans.org/features/ruby/index.html" target="_blank"&gt;NetBeans with Ruby support&lt;/a&gt; was the one that provided the best IDE experience for me so far, and for text editors I mostly used &lt;a href="http://www.scintilla.org/SciTE.html" target="_blank"&gt;Scite&lt;/a&gt; that comes with Ruby. (I do all my programming on a PC so no &lt;a href="http://macromates.com/" target="_blank"&gt;TextMate&lt;/a&gt; for me and for whatever reason &lt;a href="http://www.e-texteditor.com/" target="_blank"&gt;e&lt;/a&gt; didn’t click with me. I also tried &lt;a href="http://www.pspad.com/" target="_blank"&gt;PSPad&lt;/a&gt;, my favorite text editor for everything else, but it didn’t work with ruby. I guess my very basic knowledge of the language didn’t help either.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;So here are some of the features I like on RubyMine some of them shared by NetBeans. &lt;em&gt;Note: I’m not giving out on NetBeans since it’s free and has support for PHP.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;h3&gt;Easy code navigation.&lt;/h3&gt;  &lt;p&gt;From a view clicking in the A icon will open the proper controller and position the cursor in the right action.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;h3&gt;&lt;a href="http://blog.dynamicprogrammer.com/content/binary/WindowsLiveWriter/RubyMineanIDEforRubyRailsandsomuchmore_A03C/ScreenHunter_01%202009-03-08%2022.33.43_2.jpg"&gt;&lt;img title="ScreenHunter_01 2009-03-08 22.33.43" style="border-right: 0px; border-top: 0px; display: inline; border-left: 0px; border-bottom: 0px" height="185" alt="ScreenHunter_01 2009-03-08 22.33.43" src="http://blog.dynamicprogrammer.com/content/binary/WindowsLiveWriter/RubyMineanIDEforRubyRailsandsomuchmore_A03C/ScreenHunter_01%202009-03-08%2022.33.43_thumb.jpg" width="443" border="0" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;  &lt;p&gt;Now if you are in a controller and click in the View icon besides the action you will navigate to the view if it exist.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://blog.dynamicprogrammer.com/content/binary/WindowsLiveWriter/RubyMineanIDEforRubyRailsandsomuchmore_A03C/ScreenHunter_02%202009-03-08%2022.34.22_2.jpg"&gt;&lt;img title="ScreenHunter_02 2009-03-08 22.34.22" style="border-right: 0px; border-top: 0px; display: inline; border-left: 0px; border-bottom: 0px" height="101" alt="ScreenHunter_02 2009-03-08 22.34.22" src="http://blog.dynamicprogrammer.com/content/binary/WindowsLiveWriter/RubyMineanIDEforRubyRailsandsomuchmore_A03C/ScreenHunter_02%202009-03-08%2022.34.22_thumb.jpg" width="316" border="0" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; If the views is not available yet RubyMine will open a prompt to create it.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://blog.dynamicprogrammer.com/content/binary/WindowsLiveWriter/RubyMineanIDEforRubyRailsandsomuchmore_A03C/ScreenHunter_03%202009-03-08%2022.34.34_2.jpg"&gt;&lt;img title="ScreenHunter_03 2009-03-08 22.34.34" style="border-right: 0px; border-top: 0px; display: inline; border-left: 0px; border-bottom: 0px" height="98" alt="ScreenHunter_03 2009-03-08 22.34.34" src="http://blog.dynamicprogrammer.com/content/binary/WindowsLiveWriter/RubyMineanIDEforRubyRailsandsomuchmore_A03C/ScreenHunter_03%202009-03-08%2022.34.34_thumb.jpg" width="289" border="0" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://blog.dynamicprogrammer.com/content/binary/WindowsLiveWriter/RubyMineanIDEforRubyRailsandsomuchmore_A03C/ScreenHunter_04%202009-03-08%2022.34.48_2.jpg"&gt;&lt;img title="ScreenHunter_04 2009-03-08 22.34.48" style="border-right: 0px; border-top: 0px; display: inline; border-left: 0px; border-bottom: 0px" height="130" alt="ScreenHunter_04 2009-03-08 22.34.48" src="http://blog.dynamicprogrammer.com/content/binary/WindowsLiveWriter/RubyMineanIDEforRubyRailsandsomuchmore_A03C/ScreenHunter_04%202009-03-08%2022.34.48_thumb.jpg" width="334" border="0" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;Also some classes have a (dependencies?) icon beside its declaration that help you to browse to base classes and partial implementations&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://blog.dynamicprogrammer.com/content/binary/WindowsLiveWriter/RubyMineanIDEforRubyRailsandsomuchmore_A03C/ScreenHunter_06%202009-03-08%2022.42.26_2.jpg"&gt;&lt;img title="ScreenHunter_06 2009-03-08 22.42.26" style="border-right: 0px; border-top: 0px; display: inline; border-left: 0px; border-bottom: 0px" height="101" alt="ScreenHunter_06 2009-03-08 22.42.26" src="http://blog.dynamicprogrammer.com/content/binary/WindowsLiveWriter/RubyMineanIDEforRubyRailsandsomuchmore_A03C/ScreenHunter_06%202009-03-08%2022.42.26_thumb.jpg" width="322" border="0" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;h3&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/h3&gt;  &lt;h3&gt;Code hints and code analysis&lt;/h3&gt;  &lt;p&gt;The familiar (for ReSharper users) yellow light bulb, shows up in some cases giving you hints on how to improve your code. In this case I positioned the cursor on the ‘new’ string and the id understands that I’m referring to the new action, so it suggest to use a symbol instead.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://blog.dynamicprogrammer.com/content/binary/WindowsLiveWriter/RubyMineanIDEforRubyRailsandsomuchmore_A03C/ScreenHunter_05%202009-03-08%2022.41.49_2.jpg"&gt;&lt;img title="ScreenHunter_05 2009-03-08 22.41.49" style="border-right: 0px; border-top: 0px; display: inline; border-left: 0px; border-bottom: 0px" height="66" alt="ScreenHunter_05 2009-03-08 22.41.49" src="http://blog.dynamicprogrammer.com/content/binary/WindowsLiveWriter/RubyMineanIDEforRubyRailsandsomuchmore_A03C/ScreenHunter_05%202009-03-08%2022.41.49_thumb.jpg" width="275" border="0" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;On the right hand you have hints (yellow, red) about your code. Even on html code.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;a href="http://blog.dynamicprogrammer.com/content/binary/WindowsLiveWriter/RubyMineanIDEforRubyRailsandsomuchmore_A03C/ScreenHunter_09%202009-03-08%2022.43.13_2.jpg"&gt;&lt;img title="ScreenHunter_09 2009-03-08 22.43.13" style="border-right: 0px; border-top: 0px; display: inline; border-left: 0px; border-bottom: 0px" height="76" alt="ScreenHunter_09 2009-03-08 22.43.13" src="http://blog.dynamicprogrammer.com/content/binary/WindowsLiveWriter/RubyMineanIDEforRubyRailsandsomuchmore_A03C/ScreenHunter_09%202009-03-08%2022.43.13_thumb.jpg" width="126" border="0" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&amp;#160;&amp;#160; &lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&amp;#160; &lt;a href="http://blog.dynamicprogrammer.com/content/binary/WindowsLiveWriter/RubyMineanIDEforRubyRailsandsomuchmore_A03C/ScreenHunter_08%202009-03-08%2022.43.03_2.jpg"&gt;&lt;img title="ScreenHunter_08 2009-03-08 22.43.03" style="border-right: 0px; border-top: 0px; display: inline; border-left: 0px; border-bottom: 0px" height="130" alt="ScreenHunter_08 2009-03-08 22.43.03" src="http://blog.dynamicprogrammer.com/content/binary/WindowsLiveWriter/RubyMineanIDEforRubyRailsandsomuchmore_A03C/ScreenHunter_08%202009-03-08%2022.43.03_thumb.jpg" width="396" border="0" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;In this case makes the sensible suggestion of get rid off the B tag and replace with some CSS or the STRONG tag:&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://blog.dynamicprogrammer.com/content/binary/WindowsLiveWriter/RubyMineanIDEforRubyRailsandsomuchmore_A03C/ScreenHunter_10%202009-03-08%2022.55.14_2.jpg"&gt;&lt;img title="ScreenHunter_10 2009-03-08 22.55.14" style="border-right: 0px; border-top: 0px; display: inline; border-left: 0px; border-bottom: 0px" height="83" alt="ScreenHunter_10 2009-03-08 22.55.14" src="http://blog.dynamicprogrammer.com/content/binary/WindowsLiveWriter/RubyMineanIDEforRubyRailsandsomuchmore_A03C/ScreenHunter_10%202009-03-08%2022.55.14_thumb.jpg" width="219" border="0" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;h3&gt;Refactorings&lt;/h3&gt;  &lt;p&gt;Of course you have some Refactorings available for you.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://blog.dynamicprogrammer.com/content/binary/WindowsLiveWriter/RubyMineanIDEforRubyRailsandsomuchmore_A03C/ScreenHunter_11%202009-03-08%2022.57.20_2.jpg"&gt;&lt;img title="ScreenHunter_11 2009-03-08 22.57.20" style="border-right: 0px; border-top: 0px; display: inline; border-left: 0px; border-bottom: 0px" height="121" alt="ScreenHunter_11 2009-03-08 22.57.20" src="http://blog.dynamicprogrammer.com/content/binary/WindowsLiveWriter/RubyMineanIDEforRubyRailsandsomuchmore_A03C/ScreenHunter_11%202009-03-08%2022.57.20_thumb.jpg" width="489" border="0" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;Code analysis:&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://blog.dynamicprogrammer.com/content/binary/WindowsLiveWriter/RubyMineanIDEforRubyRailsandsomuchmore_A03C/ScreenHunter_12%202009-03-08%2022.57.32_2.jpg"&gt;&lt;img title="ScreenHunter_12 2009-03-08 22.57.32" style="border-right: 0px; border-top: 0px; display: inline; border-left: 0px; border-bottom: 0px" height="91" alt="ScreenHunter_12 2009-03-08 22.57.32" src="http://blog.dynamicprogrammer.com/content/binary/WindowsLiveWriter/RubyMineanIDEforRubyRailsandsomuchmore_A03C/ScreenHunter_12%202009-03-08%2022.57.32_thumb.jpg" width="495" border="0" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;And find usages:&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://blog.dynamicprogrammer.com/content/binary/WindowsLiveWriter/RubyMineanIDEforRubyRailsandsomuchmore_A03C/ScreenHunter_13%202009-03-08%2022.57.48_2.jpg"&gt;&lt;img title="ScreenHunter_13 2009-03-08 22.57.48" style="border-right: 0px; border-top: 0px; display: inline; border-left: 0px; border-bottom: 0px" height="210" alt="ScreenHunter_13 2009-03-08 22.57.48" src="http://blog.dynamicprogrammer.com/content/binary/WindowsLiveWriter/RubyMineanIDEforRubyRailsandsomuchmore_A03C/ScreenHunter_13%202009-03-08%2022.57.48_thumb.jpg" width="265" border="0" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://blog.dynamicprogrammer.com/content/binary/WindowsLiveWriter/RubyMineanIDEforRubyRailsandsomuchmore_A03C/ScreenHunter_14%202009-03-08%2022.58.03_2.jpg"&gt;&lt;img title="ScreenHunter_14 2009-03-08 22.58.03" style="border-right: 0px; border-top: 0px; display: inline; border-left: 0px; border-bottom: 0px" height="314" alt="ScreenHunter_14 2009-03-08 22.58.03" src="http://blog.dynamicprogrammer.com/content/binary/WindowsLiveWriter/RubyMineanIDEforRubyRailsandsomuchmore_A03C/ScreenHunter_14%202009-03-08%2022.58.03_thumb.jpg" width="448" border="0" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;h3&gt;Conclusion&lt;/h3&gt;  &lt;p&gt;This are just some of the features, for a complete list visit the JetBrains site, most of them also work in JavaScript files and html files, so you can use them in other projects not just Ruby ones.&lt;/p&gt;</Content>
